page.title: 01CRANBOURNE & WINDSOR PARK
page.content: {The region}has been studied by two Primary schools.The western area by Cranbourne County Primary,and the Eastern half by Upton House Private School,Windsor. {Cranbourne}is a small peaceful village made by ribbon development along North street,Lovel road and Hatchet lane.Most people tend to work in London. {Windsor Great Park}is a peaceful place in parts of which the public can enjoy leisure activities.The area is mainly given to either forest or farmland administered by the Crown Estates Office.Employees live in the delightful village there with its own shop and social club.There is interesting plant and wildlife and a commercial saw-mill.The most important local inhabitant is the Deputy-Head Ranger.
